\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator of the representation alludes to the following two important points made in the representation\'3A\line The curriculum for the above programme has been reviewed in its entirety \'28highlight added\'29 to address inconsistencies. The modules have now been correlated as per the Application Form and the Programme Design Summary submitted. Consequently\'2C the total credit value of the programme is 130 credits and the programme is pitched at NQF Level 5 \'28highlights added\'29.\line \line \'E2\'80\'A6.It should be noted that the module\'2C purpose\'2C credits\'2C outcomes and syllabus of the programme was erroneously submitted \'28highlight added\'29.This has been subsequently rectified. The detailed module description\'2C credits\'2C NQF Level\'2C Purpose\'2C Outcomes and Syllabus is attached as Annexure C1.\line \line In essence this implies that a new programme was now submitted and should be submitted as such. In this regard the evaluator states that the institution should re-submit the \'E2\'80\'9Ccorrect\'E2\'80\'9D programme in the form of a fresh Application for Programme Accreditation \'28Candidacy Phase\'29 incorporating the extensive information that has been supplied\'2C in relation to the relevant Criteria. It is simply illogical to evaluate what is in essence a new programme against narratives that were originally provided for a different\'2C \'28incorrect\'29 programme.\line \line The Directorate concurs that the original decision not to accredit the programme be upheld and that the institution be requested to submit a new application based on the new revised programme.\line \line \cell \pard 

